## Real World Use Case

This pipeline architecture reflects a real-world enterprise DevOps environment where multiple teams collaborate to deliver software efficiently and securely.

In modern organizations, developers continuously update application code. Manual deployments introduce risks such as inconsistent configurations, human errors, and security vulnerabilities.

This automated CI/CD pipeline solves these problems by ensuring that every code change is automatically validated, tested, scanned for vulnerabilities, and deployed in a controlled manner.

Organizations benefit from this pipeline through:

- Faster application delivery
- Reduced deployment errors
- Improved code quality
- Automated security validation
- Consistent infrastructure deployments

The GitOps model used in this project ensures that infrastructure changes are version-controlled, auditable, and reproducible.
